news.title: Haryana forest department asks district admins to come up with wetland conservation plan
news.para: Jagdish Chandra, principal chief conservator of forests (wildlife), Haryana, said, “The state has been working towards notifying wetlands and conserving them. We have already got the Ramsar tag for two of our wetlands last year.”

news.title: Maharashtra government says no to housing for retired officials on extension
news.para: In his letter, Deshmukh said in view of acute shortage of government quarters even for serving bureaucrats, it will not be possible to accommodate Shivaji and Jagtap.

news.title: Nashik: Three months extension for offline approval of building plans given before Dec 31
news.para: Earlier, December 31 was the deadline for offline submission of the building plans, and over 1,500 proposals were submitted offline in December last year.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body may increase property user charges
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) has proposed to raise user charges in property tax for residential and commercial properties.

news.title: Vadodara mayor says Sanjaynagar project to kick off soon
news.para: The housing scheme in Sanjaynagar was planned on a public-private partnership model under the Pradhan Mantri Aavas Yojana after razing 1,841 dwellings there.

news.title: Rajasthan: 1.55 lakh beneficiaries eligible for rural housing scheme
news.para: The reasons listed for rejection of names by the portal are land related issues, house related issues, income and facility related issues, document duplication related issues and other reasons.

news.title: FPCE moves SC for time-bound implementation of RERA by West Bengal government
news.para: The Supreme Court, in May last year, had struck down West Bengal government's law -- WBHIRA -- for regulating real estate sector saying it was "unconstitutional".

news.title: Karnataka housing minister greenlights work order for 10,000 houses
news.para: Housing minister V Somanna directed the authorities to finalise the beneficiaries’ list before January 31 and issue the work order to construct houses before February 10.

news.title: Karnataka: Unique land parcel number to make all papers available in one place
news.para: ​Many departments are involved in managing one land, which creates opportunities for fraudsters to create fake documents and cheat people. Once the new system is in place, Karnataka will be the first state to implement it.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP asks cops to register FIRs against 31 violators for building illegal colonies
news.para: Out of the seven police complaints against the offenders, four have been filed at Bhondsi and three at Farrukhnagar police stations. These illegal colonies, covering two to eight acres, have come up at Bhondsi, Farrukhnagar and Ghamroj in the last few months, police said.

news.title: Ramco Cements' net profit drops 59% in Q3 FY22
news.para: Net revenue of the company for the December 2021 quarter grew 16% to Rs 1,556 crore, as against Rs 1,345 crore reported in the quarter ending December, 2020.

news.title: China Evergrande shares rise as it names state firm official to board; peers sell assets
news.para: Evergrande's assets are expected to be taken over by state-owned firms in a restructuring led by the provincial government of Guangdong, where the developer is based, and the naming of an official from a unit of a state asset manager to its board could signal the restructuring was moving forward.

news.title: Kochi lacks proper streetlight system
news.para: Lack of proper monitoring and absence of staff to take care of issues related to street lighting are the main problem that lead to poor streetlight system in the city.

news.title: Can't distribute new titles in two months in Devikulam: Sources
news.para: The controversial title deeds known as ‘Raveendran pattayams’ were issued illegally by M I Raveendran, the then additional tahsildar, in 1999.

news.title: Sustainable green plan for urban areas soon: Gurugram development body
news.para: According to officials, although the GMDA Act, 2017, mandated that such a plan should be prepared “from time to time”, the district environment management plan was prepared and released by the state government, creating uncertainty about whether a separate plan was required for the GMDA areas.
